white crane
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:white heron, kotuku
Origin:[none]
Register: obsolete

Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: (the 1870 citation is a literary transf. into Eng. of a well-known Maori proverb (W.150; Neil Grove <i>Nga Peepeha a nga Tuupuna</i> (1984) no. 671): He kootuku rerenga tahi i te tau, used of a distinguished visitor who comes as rarely a the white heron),
